PrecisRegulations Amending the DAIRY PRODUCTS REGULATIONS by replacing mandatory export grading and certification requirements for butter, Cheddar cheese and dry milk powder - in bulk format - with optional organoleptic grading and certification services that will be available upon request, by repealing the grade designations Canada 2 and Canada 3 for butter and Cheddar cheese, and by requiring that registration licences be renewed on April 1 of each year.
